    {
      "id": "authorable-pieces-ports",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Port Declarations",
      "position": {
        "x": 1420,
        "y": -220
      },
      "width": 340,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Port Declarations\n\nWhat gets added to the node is not the rendered port widget itself.\n\nWhat gets added is the declaration that the node exposes boundary interfaces.\n\nCurrent architecture:\n- port declarations belong to node schema / graph structure\n- graph rendering makes them visible and interactive\n- they may coexist with the view surface\n\nCurrent law:\n- once a node explicitly declares ports, those declarations are authoritative\n- the renderer should honor them and not invent extra ports on top\n- legacy `inputs[]` / `outputs[]` are tolerated mainly for backward compatibility\n- defaults only exist when nothing explicit was declared",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
