    {
      "id": "authorable-pieces-default-rules",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Default Rules",
      "position": {
        "x": 140,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Default Rules\n\n- nodes begin empty\n- pieces are added intentionally\n- the primary inline surface is a view\n- small visible node actions are node controls\n- larger exposed surfaces are panels / secondary views\n- shell is neutral by default\n- drag and resize are **editor conventions**, not freeform authored parts\n- the default drag surface is the **type badge**\n- resize behavior should converge on one editor-level pattern\n- ports may coexist with the view surface\n- explicit ports win once declared\n- legacy ports are compatibility only\n- no forbidden combinations at this level yet\n\nThis is enough to guide authoring without freezing the architecture.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
